      • byOperator

        @NotNull
public final @NotNull TieBreaker.AssociationRuleTieBreaker byOperator(@NotNull
                                                                               @NotNull Operator operator)
        Adds an additional criteria to the current tie-breaking strategy, which performs tie-breaking according to a specific operator. I.e., if an association rule reaches a greater performance according to the given operator, it is sorted before the other one.
        Parameters:
        operator - The operator, which should be used for tie-breaking, as an instance of the type Operator. The operator may not be null
        Returns:
        The tie-breaking strategy, including the added criteria, as an instance of the class TieBreaker.AssociationRuleTieBreaker. The tie breaking-strategy may not be null

public final @NotNull TieBreaker.AssociationRuleTieBreaker preferSimple()
        Adds an additional criteria to the current tie-breaking strategy, which prefers simple association rules over complex ones. I.e., if an association rule contains less items than its counterpart in its body and head, it is sorted before the other one.
        Returns:
        The tie-breaking strategy, including the added criteria, as an instance of the class TieBreaker.AssociationRuleTieBreaker. The tie breaking-strategy may not be null

      • custom

        @NotNull
public final @NotNull TieBreaker.AssociationRuleTieBreaker custom(@NotNull
                                                                           @NotNull java.util.Comparator<AssociationRule> comparator)
        Adds an additional custom criteria to the current tie-breaking strategy. The given comparator must return 1, if the first association rule should be preferred, -1, if the second one should be preferred or 0, if no decision could be made.
        Parameters:
        comparator - The comparator, which specifies which one of two item sets or association rules should be sorted before the other one when performing tie-breaking, as an instance of the type Comparator. The comparator may not be null
        Returns:
        The tie-breaking strategy, including the added criteria, as an instance of the class TieBreaker.AssociationRuleTieBreaker. The tie breaking-strategy may not be null
